TITLE: Southwest’s Meltdown Could Cost It Up to $825 Million
SUMMARY: The airline has not said how soon it will upgrade the systems that contributed to mass flight cancellations, or how much that will cost.

TITLE: Stranded by Southwest and Stuck With Unexpected Costs
SUMMARY: The airline’s customers incurred thousands in expenses as they scrambled to find alternate ways to get home.

TITLE: U.S. employers added 223,000 jobs in December.
SUMMARY: Forecasters estimate that employers added 200,000 jobs in December, a robust number though a bit below the average in recent months.

TITLE: Markets Rise as Investors Like the Look of Hiring and Wage Trends
SUMMARY: Traders are betting that a slowdown in job growth and wage gains could reduce the pressure on prices and make the Federal Reserve less aggressive in raising interest rates.

TITLE: Republicans’ Internecine Conflict Is Mirrored in Conservative Media
SUMMARY: National Review has called the House leadership votes “an embarrassing spectacle.” Others have cheered it on.

TITLE: Eurozone Inflation Eases on Lower Energy Prices
SUMMARY: The rate of price increases in countries using the euro slowed to 9.2 percent in December, down from 10.1 percent a month earlier.

TITLE: For Freelancers, New Federal Help in Saving for Retirement
SUMMARY: The Secure 2.0 Act provides for direct government contributions to retirement accounts for low- and moderate-income workers, though that won’t start until 2027.

TITLE: S.E.C. Inquiry Into Former Senator’s Stock Sales Is Closed Without Charges
SUMMARY: The Securities and Exchange Commission ended its investigation into former Senator Richard Burr, three years after he sold more than $1.6 million in stocks following Covid-19 briefings.

TITLE: FDA Approves, Leqembi, New Treatment for Early Alzheimer’s
SUMMARY: The drug, Leqembi, may modestly slow cognitive decline in early stages of the disease but carries some safety risks. Still, data suggests it is more promising than the small number of other available treatments.

TITLE: Tensions with Virgin Islands Governor Over Epstein Led to Attorney General’s Firing
SUMMARY: Denise George, who led a three-year investigation into the activities of Jeffrey Epstein, was fired recently.

TITLE: What Shows Like ‘Kaleidoscope’ Tell Us About Streaming and TV
SUMMARY: A decade of bingeing has transformed storytelling and viewing habits. But we may be starting to hit that transformation’s limits.

TITLE: Why Bed Bath & Beyond Is Weighing Bankruptcy
SUMMARY: Dreary holiday season sales failed to help solve the struggling retailer’s financial woes, leaving the company with few options.

TITLE: Financial Planning for Retirement: It’s More Accessible, but Be Careful
SUMMARY: Financial planning and advice is no longer just for the wealthy. It can be especially important when planning for your later years.

TITLE: Help! A Check-in Agent’s Mistake Made Me Miss an Antarctic Cruise and I’m Out $17,000.
SUMMARY: An American Airlines error kept a traveler from getting to her cruise’s departure, but the carrier wouldn’t take financial responsibility and her trip insurance refused to pay. Then our columnist stepped in.

TITLE: Even a Soft Landing for the Economy May Be Uneven
SUMMARY: Small businesses and lower-income families could feel pinched in the months ahead whether or not a recession is avoided this year.

TITLE: How a Texas Border City Is Shaping the Future of Global Trade
SUMMARY: Laredo, across from Mexico on the Rio Grande, is primed to become one of the world’s most important land ports as American companies reduce their reliance on factories in Asia.

TITLE: A Breach at LastPass Has Password Lessons for Us All
SUMMARY: The hacking of the password manager should make us reassess whether to trust companies to store our sensitive data in the cloud.

TITLE: Mercedes-Benz Plans to Build U.S. Electric Car Charging Network
SUMMARY: The network could help increase the low number of charging stations, encouraging more people to buy electric vehicles.

TITLE: New York Attorney General Sues Founder of Collapsed Crypto Bank
SUMMARY: Letitia James accused the founder of Celsius Network, Alex Mashinsky, of a scheme to defraud hundreds of thousands of investors.

TITLE: Ford Sales Dipped in 2022, but Electric Vehicle Deliveries Surged
SUMMARY: The company’s production was limited by a global chip shortage, but it made big gains in the fastest-growing segment of the auto market.

TITLE: CVS and Walgreens Plan to Offer Abortion Pills Where Abortion Is Legal
SUMMARY: The two chains said they would begin the certification process under a new F.D.A. regulation that will allow retail pharmacies to dispense the prescription pills for the first time.

TITLE: Tesla Sales in China Slump as Competition Intensifies
SUMMARY: Worry about the carmaker’s sales in the world’s largest car market is one reason the shares have plunged.

TITLE: U.S. Moves to Bar Noncompete Agreements in Labor Contracts
SUMMARY: A sweeping proposal by the Federal Trade Commission would block companies from limiting their employees’ ability to work for a rival.

TITLE: Bed Bath & Beyond Warns of Possible Bankruptcy
SUMMARY: The home goods retailer said weak sales and slower foot traffic had forced it to consider options for restructuring.

TITLE: Kevin McCarthy’s Business Ties Complicate His Rise to Power
SUMMARY: To land the House speaker position, the California Republican will have to win over opponents who question his ties to Silicon Valley and his commitment to right wing causes.

TITLE: Amazon Expands Corporate Layoffs to 18,000 Jobs
SUMMARY: The layoffs will focus on human resources and its retail division, Amazon’s chief executive said in an email to employees.

TITLE: James ‘Buster’ Corley, Co-Founder of Dave & Buster’s, Dies at 72
SUMMARY: The chain appealed to adults by combining food, beverage, sports and gaming under one roof.

TITLE: Fed Officials Fretted That Markets Would Misread Rate Slowdown
SUMMARY: Central bankers remained committed to wrestling inflation lower, and wanted to make sure investors understood that message, minutes from the Federal Reserve’s December meeting showed.

TITLE: Labor Market Strength Persisted Heading Into the Holidays
SUMMARY: Government data from November showed job openings remained high, with rates of quitting and layoffs holding steady.

TITLE: Former CNN Digital Chief Named Publisher of Atlanta Journal-Constitution
SUMMARY: Andrew Morse, who was an architect of CNN+, plans to team up with Axios to expand the newspaper’s digital business.

TITLE: Fed Official Compares Inflation to Uber Surge Pricing
SUMMARY: Neel Kashkari, the president of the Minneapolis Fed, kicked off 2023 monetary policy debates with a call for better understanding of what causes inflation.

TITLE: Meta Fined $414 Million After Ad Practices Ruled Illegal Under EU Law
SUMMARY: The decision is one of the most consequential issued under the E.U.’s landmark data-protection law and creates a new business headwind for the social media giant.

TITLE: Supply Problems Hurt Auto Sales in 2022. Now Demand Is Weakening.
SUMMARY: A global semiconductor shortage is easing, which could allow carmakers to lift production this year. But higher interest rates could keep sales low.

TITLE: Coinbase Reaches $100 Million Settlement With New York Regulators
SUMMARY: The U.S. crypto exchange will pay a $50 million fine for letting customers open accounts with few background checks and spend $50 million to improve compliance.

TITLE: Salesforce to Lay Off 10 Percent of Staff and Cut Office Space
SUMMARY: The software company plans to cut around 8,000 jobs as business slows for tech companies. “We hired too many people leading into this economic downturn,” Salesforce’s chief executive said.

TITLE: Tesla Investors Fear for a Tough 2023
SUMMARY: A huge sell-off wiped billions of dollars from the electric carmaker’s market capitalization on Tuesday. Analysts see more trouble ahead.

TITLE: Bruce’s Beach: L.A. County to Buy Land Seized from Black Family
SUMMARY: California officials seized a beachfront property from Willa and Charles Bruce in 1924. Los Angeles County returned it to their great-grandsons last year. Now they’re selling it back.

TITLE: Why Are Energy Prices So High? Some Experts Blame Deregulation.
SUMMARY: California and the 34 other states that have deregulated all or parts of their electricity system tend to have higher rates than the rest of the country.

TITLE: Need an Onion? These Indian Apps Will Deliver It in Minutes.
SUMMARY: Fueled by billions of dollars in investments, Indian companies are rushing to cut delivery prices and wait times, relying on an army of low-paid, harried drivers.

TITLE: Father Deliberately Drove Car Off Cliff, Authorities Say After Dramatic Rescue
SUMMARY: Dharmesh A. Patel was arrested on suspicion of attempted murder and child abuse after his Tesla careened off a treacherous cliff in Northern California with him, his wife and two children inside, the authorities said.

SUMMARY: The question everyone wanted to know, including those at the sports network: What had happened to Damar Hamlin, and would he be OK?

TITLE: Video Game Workers Get a Union Foothold at Microsoft
SUMMARY: The outcome, involving about 300 employees, is one of organized labor’s biggest victories at a major U.S. tech company.

TITLE: Sam Bankman-Fried Pleads Not Guilty to Fraud and Other Charges
SUMMARY: The founder of the collapsed cryptocurrency exchange FTX, who was released on a $250 million bond, returned to New York to appear in court on Tuesday.

SUMMARY: With Prince Harry’s new book, “Spare,” set to be released next week, Britain is gearing up for the release of revealing new interviews with the estranged royal.

TITLE: Natural Gas Prices in Europe Fall to Pre-Invasion Levels
SUMMARY: Warm weather, alternatives to Russian gas and a buildup of storage all help. But prices remain high for consumers and industry.

TITLE: Markets Slip in First Session of 2023
SUMMARY: Analysts are more cautious about 2023 after their overly optimistic forecasts for last year.

SUMMARY: Intense legal wrangling led to the disgraced crypto mogul paying virtually nothing to live with his parents ahead of his upcoming trial. He returns to court on Tuesday.

TITLE: Wave of Job-Switching Has Employers on a Training Treadmill

TITLE: Biden Caps Two Years of Action on the Economy, With New Challenges Ahead
SUMMARY: The president used a slim congressional majority to enact legislation that could reshape the American economy — if his administration can make the laws succeed.

TITLE: Tesla Car Sales Grow Slower Than Expected, Amplifying Concerns
SUMMARY: Wall Street has grown decidedly pessimistic about Tesla, fearful that Elon Musk, its chief executive, is too focused on Twitter.

SUMMARY: Lower-cost liquor could help the emirate keep its edge over neighbors like Saudi Arabia and Qatar as the Middle East’s hub for leisure and business.

TITLE: Jeremy Renner Is in Critical Condition After Snow Plowing Accident
SUMMARY: The actor, known for his role as Hawkeye in Marvel’s Avengers movies, had surgery, his representative said.

TITLE: Why China’s Economy Faces a Perilous Road to Recovery
SUMMARY: Years of lockdowns took a brutal toll on businesses. Now, the rapid spread of Covid after a chaotic reopening has deprived them of workers and customers.
